caption: Best food, friendly staff members, regularly great atmosphere. They charge reasonable pricing and the food quality is awesome. Keep it up.

We make sure to come back to this place everytime we visit Baltimore.  One of our favorite Indian take out places we have visited throughout our travels.  The berry ginger ale and the gobi Manchurian are always standing orders for us.
The place serves big portions and for convenient prices. helpful owner. Will visit again.

Amidst pandemic, we decided to visit Baltimore aquarium which was good & ended up walking to this Indian place for food. The owner seemed friendly & followed all the current safety procedures. I believe he's the waiter & cook...the less through better, right? He made excellent panner curries, indo-chinese noodles & fried rice. We will definitely visit the place again.
Great food! Very friendly service. Exactly what you want.

One of my favorite Indian restaurants in Baltimore! Have gotten delivery from them a couple of times and they give big portion sizes for the money. Very good food – especially love the Szechuan potatoes. Love having a place with good Indian Chinese options in Baltimore!
Good portion size for Carryout. Butter chicken curry had a good balance of sweet and spicy.

I would not recommend anyone to go in this Restaurant. It's food is too old which will make your health too worst. And even they guys are not cooking new food it's old food frozen food, i had order Garlic Naan and it was frozen naan which taste something else. Even his vegetable birayni was not having good taste. I order it and it was given me in less than a 15 minute which can be clearly seen it was an old. Overall, it's your health it depends on you if you want to play with your health🙏🏻🙏🏻.

My boyfriend and I came to this restaurant a couple of weeks ago. The food was amazing and plentiful! I was stuffed and still had enough food for two meals. Amazing prices, plenty of food, and a quaint atmosphere.

The food and presentation of the food was awesome. Great portion sizes for a party which allow your table to dig in at their leisure. At first we questioned why it was taking so long but it seemed like just the kind of night for a one man show but regardless once the food reached our table we were extremely please at the wonderful and service provided. Will definitely be returning
The place has a nice feel to it.
Great environment and super affable service. The meals were crisp and enchanting. Will clearly recommend this restaurant to anyone. Convenient prices and generous meals. Good job.
Delicious curries
It was so savory. Certainly worth a return trip.

This is an amazing place to eat. The food was amazing that we called back and said thank you for the amazing food. I’m from India and it took me back. Try it and you will fall in love. It’s as good as my moms food.
Nice n cool 👍👍👍

My wife ( Indian born) and I usually  eat Indian dish. I ordered mostly, Chicken or lamb Curry which is my favorite usually, with garlic or cheese naan and Samosas. My first time ordering  my usual Indian food from here, was the one time I’ve complained about Indian food being so bad. For short, the food was a mess. The curry was nothing like lamb curry (more like meatball ravioli) but tomato sauce. The garlic naan and samosas were completely burnt and too salty.. I called the restaurant and the person who answered the phone just gaff me off and didn’t take any responsibility but, told me that it was what I ordered. If this was my first time eating Indian food in my life, I would have never dare to try it again.

A rare gem in an area not otherwise known, with a few exceptions, for great dining. Little India Cafe is tucked away in an unassuming strip mall, but its worth finding! The three of us ate like princes for under $23/head on flavorful, nicely prepared and presented, well-portioned lamb, chicken, shrimp, dishes served piping hot with wonderful sauces. The Indian Feast was multi-coursed and fit for three, but we supplemented it with tandoor grilled prawns, and came away stuffed and happy. Attentive staff, Indian-themed setting. We'll be back!
What a phenomenal delivery option! Their food is amazing and comes very quickly.  Everything tastes freshly prepared and healthy.  Possibly the best Indian food in Baltimore.
They serve rats and cats and dogs in their food

My wife and I eat Indian food often. Chicken Biryani is my wife's favorite and I traditionally get the Butter Chicken. We ordered out usual along with Garlic Naan and Samosas. What was supposed to be Chicken Biryani, was just White rice and very little chicken, the garlic naan and samosas were completely burnt and not edible. I called and the person on the phone blamed doordash. Not taking responsibility for the food that they sent.  Ridiculous
Too expensive.
A good place to visit food is also good need few more variety need more items ..
Cheap and delicious
Wrong Little India
Love the buffet here! great food, the butter chicken and chilli chicken is especially good. and the Nunn as well. interesting boss and nice? to talk to.
Aromatics galore, tons of dishes @ the lunch buffet! Hot soft fresh yummy naan too!!
Worst food I ever had!!!
The food is okay. Not expensive. Services are good.
The best Indian food I've had.

I often take my friends to this restaurant with my highest recommendations. I  go to this restaurant often. I get very good feedback from my friends. The the cooking is delicious and the stuff is generous and cooperative. Every time  we eat in this place we pass a lovely time.  I recommend this place with pleasure.
Great food!
Delish buffet!
I admire this venue very much. there is a very nice mood. The cuisine is exeptionaly good. the service is powerful and the team is friendly. The price is decent. I definitely recommend.

It was a little different than I'm used to from Indian food, but I really enjoyed it.  The Tikka masala had big chunks of chicken, but they were delicious, along with peppers and onions and was well spiced.  The naan was very firm, almost like a cross between a biscuit and a tortilla, again, unexpected but very delicious.  Portions are generous, despite my best efforts I couldn't even get through half of it. I recommend take out or delivery though, the restaurant itself is a little dive-y, but seemed to be clean and we'll taken care of.
Very well kept and accessible spot. They serve large portions and for fair prices. We enjoyed the food very much and the waiters were very affable and explanatory. Recommended.
Very good food

I've tried about 30 different Indian restaurants around Baltimore alone .......this one is the best.....it all comes down to taste and their cooking is amazing ......cant beat the value either , a true gem , especially the lunch buffets
Sucks
Great food and service
Nice small Indian restaurant.  Staff very kind and welcoming,  tasty food in buffet. May be a limited choice for dessert. I recommend
Good food

Horrible restaurant, got food poisoning, was sick for 2 days!  Called restaurant to report this-my call was ignored but they took my money.  I don’t advise eating here.  They did not have the courage & decency to follow up with me the customer.  I believe they re-serve old food from a buffet bar & it was what made me extremely ill!
The food was authentic and the service was wonderful. However, coming from suburbia I found parking to be a challenge in the city.

This was one of the few places open for a late lunch. We ordered paneer tikka masala, naan, chicken biryani and samosa chat. The chat had too any onions, else it was really good. My friends really liked their biryani. The paneer tikka masala was good too. Adequate amount of spice! Their portions are good sized so order carefully! The samosa chat was enough for me and my friend.
(Translated by Google) A small restaurant in Baltimore is just as simple as inside  (Original) बाल्टिमोर में छोटी सा रेस्टॉरेंट शक्ल में अंदर से बिल्कुल साधारण सा
Solid choice, great customer service
It is the best place if you want to taste Indian food.

We were served burned food and forced to pay for it, we never touched it. The server was rude and angry towards us for using a groupon. He argued with us for not know the restaurant rules for coupons. Some of our ordered food was served to us from the buffet.  Never again!
Good food👍✌️Best place for Indian food 👌✌️
This is an excellent Indian restaurant.  The lunch buffet is great with very nice fresh offerings.  The place is a bit dated and can use a freshening up but the food is very good!
Food was very good for lunch buffet and the price was reasonable. They just didn’t refill fast enough for the number of people that came in.
Lunch buffet was tasty, although I am unfamiliar with some of the items offered. I enjoyed everything I tried, and will be returning!
Wish it was better
Great buffet, excellent cooking, friendly hosts
The food and service is awesome. I definitely will be back to try out the buffet.
Amazing service and best Indian cuisine I've had.  Atmosphere makes you feel at home. Will definitely be returning again.
Great food, reasonable price!!!!
Great food, good service, clean place
Worst place to have food, the owner does not know what customer service means. The place is small, cramped and unpleasant to say the least. Avoid at any cost.

Very tasty lunch buffet food, very clean, and friendly waiter. Small cozy place in little Italy. Very easy to find, street parking is a bit difficult though. Highly recommend for Budget lunch. College student friendly prices.
Place looks fantastic. You can see some chefs cooking. Food tastes amazing. Service is unbeatable. Food came really fast. Worth the high price.
I love Indian food and this place serves the best out of it. Gonna visit them again.
one of the best indian restaurant in baltimore.
Tasty food with most modest and pleasant environment. And i liked their services and the way they look after their customers. Must visit place for all.
Food was very outstanding. If you're looking great Indian food, THIS IS THE PLACE TO GO!

Very decent indian food. Huge portions. I wanted to meet a friend who lives close by and we ended up here. I ordered Chana Masala (which came with a lot of rice) and she ordered some chicken dish, we also ordered one naan (which was enough for the two of us). The hospitality staff was incredible and the food tasted good.

Best indian food I've had in Baltimore (aside from the late, great Mughal Gardens, that is). Upon reading reviews, all I can say is that I personally have not yet had a bad experience here. They are especially good about spicing the dish to your preferences. There appetizers are fantastic as well.

While we were in Baltimore, I found this Indian restaurant which is opened few months back. Good taste and nice buffet . It’s Good place to visit. They made Paneer Saang for my child which was not part of their buffet. 👍  😀

The service was fantastic and the food was very good.  There was no wait to be seated and a very short wait for the food. The bathroom was clean. If I'm in town again, I'll definitely  be coming back.

I'm a North Indian guy, so I believe I have the capability to judge this cuisine. The food was very well cooked and very tasty. It tastes similar to authentic Indian cuisine. Nice customer service, quality (Cooked in Desi Ghee aka clarified butter) and portion size. If you're in a Baltimore area, it's a must recommend Indian restaurant.

First time visit. Excellent service and excellent food!  We were sat promptly without a reservation on a busy Friday night and very well taken care of. If not for living out of the USA I would definitely be back!

Great food! We ate off the buffet. It seems like a one man operation here, at least on dec 30th, which explains why every dish on the buffet wasn’t full, but who cares! If you’re coming for “atmosphere” and a “food scene” this isn’t the place for you, but if you want real deal Indian at a low price, than eat here! Naan made fresh and fantastically well. Sure, the building is old and the bathrooms are “spick and span” but so what! You came here for the food.
The most horrible indian food I ever had. It's not even worth a one star rating.

Worst experience ever. Awful bathroom, extremely smelly place, dirty ambiance and very rude chef. Says something and offer something else, can't trust this place ever again. I ll never go to this place.
I go very frequently and it js always very satisfying with very good prices, especially for the buffet.
The place could have been cleaner and the waiter was alone and wasn't attentive. Food was good but not the best Indian food I ever had!

Small place in the corner of little Italy which offers good indian food. My entire experience was spoiled by the manager constantly shouting over phone about some misplaced order which IMO could have been handled differently.

Went here with a Groupon. The place could have been cleaner and the waiter wasn't very attentive. There were only a handful of people there on the Wednesday night I went. BYOB so bring a bottle of wine, if that's your thing. Food was good though. If you like spicy, get the avocado banana chaat - SO GOOD. The rosemary naan was good but not the best I've had.

Outstanding flavor and selection in the buffet. My only critique was the food had obviously been out for awhile,  in other words "not freshly cooked"; however, it was still wonderful. If I could deduct half a star I would, so in this case it's 5 stars.
Amazing food! We went for lunch buffet and every dish was exceptional! An impressive variety as  well. Perhaps the best Indian food I have ever had at a restaurant.

Average food, average prices, LOTS of little flies around the food, place smelled musty, bathroom dirty & stinky. When it was time to pay, we told them we had a Groupon and the server made a huge deal of it saying that we were supposed to tell them in ADVANCE that we had a Groupon..... why? Would they have prepared our food differently or treated us differently, maybe given us smaller portions? We spent more than double of the Groupon value. Won't be going back.
This is the best indian cousin restaurant in town. I love the food here and Mr. Chekhar (owner) is a nice person with positive attitude.

Came here in the winter and had a fine experience, decided to give it a second try. The appetizer was lukewarm and the lamb entree was extremely chewy and dry. The server gave us our check without prompting, then informed us that they would be unable to honor our Groupon since we had not notified them at the beginning of the meal. Management was unapologetic and not interested in attempting to reconcile with us. Of note, there was another customer in the restaurant who also was unable to redeem their Groupon- so clearly this is a recurrent issue. We will certainly not return.

good food, authentic indian vibe and all that. But the waiter was really too clumsy and food came way too late. He served the appetizer 15 minutes after serving the main dish, five minutes after that there came the sides ordered with main dish. I saw him arguing with another customer who had a groupon.

Don't be deterred by the looks, the flavor is spot on.  I assume the modesty of the decor helps keep this place reasonably priced.  Maybe the best chana masala I've  ever had.  The chicken curry was also great.  Friendly staff.  Great carry out option with the lunch buffet.

Little India is in Little Italy and the only non-Italian restaurant in Baltimore's Little Italy. Because of this, you assume it isn't good, but mark my words- Little India is some of the best Indian food on the East Coast. It's a small restaurant, but they do have two areas of table. They have a buffet, but if you like butter chicken, just order that. My wife and I got two servings of butter chicken (the sauce is so creamy), jasmine rice, mango chutney, and naan. We did takeover and it took twenty minutes (explore Little Italy as you wait). The portions are healthy and you can stretch the butter chicken to dinner and lunch!
The chicken marsala was phenomenal. The service was courteous and attentive.
We came this place Group after made call 2hrs back most food finsh.Our group filled downstairs. We ask them to served food downstairs they didn't do  it...
Decent buffet for a quick lunch on a workday.
Have had the lunch buffet a few times and picked up chicken korma for dinner. Their lunch buffet is a great deal and the seating is good for one on one conversations
A very flavorful buffet.  Richer than most Indian buffets.

This little joint is a gem. There's not a huge crowd but there's a huge flavor in their food! The lunch buffet is well rounded, offering 4 meat dishes, an appetizer, two rice, 4 veg, and dessert. My fave is the channa saag. It combines the awesome flavors of two of my fave dishes in one! The staff is overwhelmingly friendly, the naan is tasty, the chai is legit fresh made when u order... I could go on for days. I love this place and so should u.
Pathetic food. Don’t even consider going here...
Good taste with great service...

If you like spicy or hot food you must make sure to ask for it though else you might just get the regular mild flavor which is too weak. Reasonable prices: Not too high but definitely not on the lower side. Plus punt is that portion sizes are good so one main dish combo is good for two people. Good feels well made. Watch out for the dahi in the raita though, could be sour. If so, ask for a change. Biggest plus is byob. So it is actually a good place to hang out for a few friends with beers for the chakna. Normal filmy love songs for music though. (The decor is not the romantic type so forget it)

My 1st order was via grub hub and I found this place promising however 2nd order was not upto the mark but I still decided to go to the restaurant and have dinner there instead and ended up giving 2 stars..  Reason: Food is OK but serious concern with the hygiene., The way table was cleant was very bad and one can find food stuck in the deep ends of the chairs of all the tables. If this is the standard of hygiene maintained at the seating area I really doubt for the kitchen and didn't dare to see it or ask the server to take me.  Not visiting or ordering again!
Nothing fancy inside but we were the only table and got great service. Looks like the restaurant was mostly serving delivery orders.
Delicious food with great service. I won't say it's the cheapest in comparison to others within a mile.

We got all vegan food so can't speak to the meat selections, but everything we got - channa masala, aloo gobi, samosas, pakoras, tamarind rice, garlic naan - was really delicious. True, the setting is a little dingy, but you can't eat decor. The gentleman working the front was very helpful and extremely nice. Highly recommend <3
Decent buffet options at fair price
Good variety

I had requested that the food be vegan and without cilantro. A woman called tell me that she recommending modifying my order in order to be vegan. I was really impressed that she called. She sounded like she really cared about my dietary needs and wanted me to be a happy customer. Unfortunately, even though I asked that the driver call me and leave the food at the front desk, He did not call. I went down to the lobby at the expected time of arrival and ended up waiting over 30 minutes. I then went to the front desk and saw a brown paper bag and asked if it was for me and it in fact was. The person at the front desk told me that he asked the driver if he had called me and he said yes but he in fact did not. Not only had I wasted 30 minutes but my food was cold and did not taste good. The jasmine rice was small and mealy. The roti it was super dry and hard and difficult to tear or chew. The gobi Manchuria was overly sauced and cooked in a way that the cauliflower was unrecognizable. The texture more resembled that of super dried, leathery chicken. Needless to say, I would not order from them again.
Food was authentic indian dining. Ambience and interior should have been better.
Good Food
Tradatinal Indian Food not very spicy as it is customized for western pallets. Good lunch Buffet for $ 9.55 on weekday and 10.55 on weekends.
My favorite bhindi masala in the city!

Lunch Buffet was a good value. Interesting dishes, especially vegetable oriented ones. Convenient to the inner harbor. Friendly people. The "traditional" chicken dishes had a different flavor that was interesting. Definitely worth the short walk from the edge of the Inner Harbor. They make the Nan fresh (Garlic and Plain) and bring it to the table. This is currently my sign for an excellent Indian Buffet.
Price is higher than food quality

DO NOT do the lunch buffet. I ate at the restaurant a month ago at 1pm, about halfway through their lunch. Food was lukewarm and heated by chafing dishes. Now I know those are signs of possible food poisoning. I went home with the "runs" until the evening.
amazing all you can eat for like $11
Fantastic deal, and excellent food.
Fantastic Indian cuisine, reasonable price and byob,ignore the decor...
Excellent food in a quaint atmosphere and very nice staff.
Best food in the area
Nice buffet and reasonably priced. Very low key.
Time pass place.  The only reason we go there is because it's the only desi food closer to work.
Food sucks, biryani is made in rice cooker Honestly you shouldn't be going here

I like delivering Grub Hub orders from here at Little India. He's Five Star Fast. I see he has a buffet going on and I'm one the road. I'd like to invite some of the taste-testers to give their take on the food. He's prompt. Appears he has a buffet set up at times. Right in Little India on Aliceanna St. Stop in and rub Bhudda's belly or have it brought to you with Grub Hub.
Best lunch special in town!
It's a quiet place. Food is okay. Not as great as other Indian restaurants. Good for a quick bite though. Not many options.

Food and price
Combo lunch is not so good..less options

Opened under new management 4 months ago-fair prices and quantity , especially the thali. Have been here before during previous management, now is by far the best. Good for frequenters to Indian restaurant, for their prices and good quality food! Will ask them next time, if they have a monthly discount for Thalis.
Outstanding food. Had the vegan tofu and peas. It rocked. Better Indian food than anywhere in DC.

Went here for the lunch buffet, and for the price, I expected a lot of non meat options. But they had goat, lamb and chicken options available. The service was on point with fresh naan brought out and the food was really good.
Poor restaurant, worst food. The restaurant is smelly and not maintained. The samosas and naan they served were almost burnt. I will NEVER go there again.
Not a fan of curry but loved this place
Food options are limited in Buffet lunch. But the quality is good. Food was tasty. The price is also low.
Really authentic
Food was well seasoned, well portioned and and decently priced. Service was good as well!
fair prices

Great food for a great price, the ambience was nice, casual and a good place to take your family and friends.food was on point all the meat is halal! how much better can it get. it cant this place is just amazing
Best butter chicken I've had. Great service. Would recommended to anyone.
Great place. Shekhar (owner) is a nice guy.
Had the lamb garlic naan and chick peas. Everything was great and lamb was moist. Manager gave us free desert.
Good food and Good Service. Under the new management they have improved a lot in terms of food quality and service. Was on a business trip in Baltimore, visited two days for dinner, not disappointed!

I ordered for delivery in Feb firstweek 2013 sometime. At that time it(Malai Kofta) was not tasty at all.  I thought may be at that time it was not good. Let me try again, so I called this restaurant and tried to order CHANNA MASALA. I told person (like 60+) that Last time it was not tasty. I just said that .... oh man.. He started angrily on phone without listen further. And he did not give me time to finish my sentence even, he cut the phone... I was surprised. I don't know how they can run business without having good hospitality. Food - Poor-Fair Decor - Poor-Fair (I dont know about Decor. Because I did not visit restaurant personally. But as you have to select option that's why I selected this option.) Service- Worse...There has to be another category ..like "DO NOT GO" Date was 2/26/13 6:30PM.

Great food!  The restaurant is a bit outdated and feels a bit tacky. When we first went in at about 6:30 pm we were the only people in there and we were a bit skeptikal.  We went a ahead and ordered a bottle of wine for only $20 which was surprisingly good.  We than proceed to order some Meat and Vegetable Samosas.  Both offering were very good.  You get one per order but they are very large so we should have ordered just one to share for two people.  There were four of us and we ordered vindaloo, tiki masala, shahi paneer, and butter chicken as well as naan.  Everything was very well seasoned and tasted absolutely delicious.  They do cater to Americans and allow you to specify wether you want your curry mild, medium or hot.  at the end of my meal I had a chai tea which was a perfect ending to my meal! P.S.  By the time we left a couple of hours later (we lingered) the restautrant was full of other customers.  I would definitely recommend this place to any of my friends and will return myself.

My first Indian food experience in Baltimore. The. Best. Home-cooked. Taste. Ever. Period. I grew up in India and moved to the US about 10 years ago. This restaurant has cooking the closest to home cooking that I've seen anywhere (even compared to restaurants back home...). Really great taste. The ambiance adds to the authentic experience. Hehe, once you step inside, there is no indication that you are in the US anymore (except for Dr. Oz on the TV). Everything (even the ceiling tiles and tacky art on the walls) seems to transport you back to a dhaba/restaurant in Punjab. On the upside, the food also transports you to that very same dhaba in Punjab.  Very very good. Looking forward to eating good Indian food here many times to come.  Caveat: First visit. Only tried vegetarian Samosa and Eggplant. Do not know about the rest of the menu (yet...).
